body: Merging this. I believe these tests will be run but not via maven.  We also should consider running a subset of T2 tests as part of PR check so that these issues are caught by the contributor

Please create a new JIRA for this and a new PR so that this change is different from [TRAFODION-1706].  I am assuming that this change deals with apache hbase (vanilla hbase) installation via Trafodion installer while 1706 deals with supporting Trafodion with hbase 1.0 in general.

https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TRAFODION-1927

This has been created.

Also Aven and I are working to get this merged in with changes from me and
some more testing.

jenkins, extra test - trigger typo, missing branch
jenkins, retest please -- hbase/zookeeper issues in previous test run unrelated to this change.
Thanks for fixing this problem! I recently tried using ilh_cleanhb and it failed because the Zookeeper directories had changed.
Why do the copyrights say "Apache Trafodion" instead of "Apache Software Foundation"?
That is a heck of a good question. I was only paying attention to updating the year, but I think you are correct. It should match the copyright that is in the NOTICE file -- ASF.
Looks good to me. I'm ready to commit if the author is also happy with it.

I am not sure. I am not clear from the response if the date/time/timestamp never worked in any flavor. In other words what is the value maxLen as returned from SQL for DATE, TIME and TIMESTAMP columns
@selvaganesang You are right. I check the value returned from SQL , it's 10 for DATE. So I change the  fix to  just remove the hardcode.  I don't know why jdbc t2 hardcode the maxLen to 26 before.
Looks good to me. Does this look right to you, @selvaganesang?
Great. Good to go in now
I am volunteering to review this code. Please give me some time to read this change.
Just checking... is there further action on this pull request?
Note: Just the multi-cluster support is disabled. Vanilla Apache support is enabled.
Looks good. A few minor code comments. Did not look too closely at the multi-cluster stuff.
Are there official instructions to follow to install the vanilla apache release, if, for example I would like to try it out?
@robertamarton I have some instructions above in the pull-request but I will work on something more official :)
Do you want to consider using hbase classpath instead of setting the classpath manually in sqenvcom.sh.
@selvaganesang I think we can address that in the sqenvcom.sh jira I created. Thanks.
